<p><b>TextMate</b> is a general-purpose <a href="/wiki/Graphical_user_interface" title="Graphical user interface">GUI</a> <a href="/wiki/Text_editor" title="Text editor">text editor</a> for <a href="/wiki/Mac_OS_X" title="Mac OS X">Mac OS X</a> created by <a href="/w/index.php?title=Allan_Odgaard&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Allan Odgaard (page does not exist)">Allan Odgaard</a>. Its users are mostly programmers<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>, though it has been used for <a href="/wiki/Screenwriting" title="Screenwriting">screenwriting</a> <sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup>. Notable features include <a href="/wiki/Declarative_programming" title="Declarative programming">declarative</a> customizations, <a href="/wiki/Tab_(GUI)" title="Tab (GUI)">tabs for open documents</a>, recordable <a href="/wiki/Macro_(computer_science)#Application_macros" title="Macro (computer science)">macros</a>, <a href="/wiki/Folding_editor" title="Folding editor">folding sections</a> and <a href="/wiki/Snippet_management" title="Snippet management" class="mw-redirect">snippets</a>, <a href="/wiki/Shell_(computing)" title="Shell (computing)">shell</a> integration, and an extensible bundle system.</p>
<p>TextMate 1.5 won the <a href="/wiki/Apple_Design_Awards" title="Apple Design Awards">Apple Design Award</a> for best developer tool in <a href="/wiki/2006" title="2006">2006</a>.</p>
